President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Connecticut due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Sandy. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to the local population. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be funded at 75 percent by the federal government. Albert Lewis has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.